### 2. Active Working Group Drafts

#### [3.1 Deployment Options](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-srv6ops-srv6-deployment-00)
* **Presenter:** Himanshu Shah (Ciena)
* **Draft Reference:** [draft-ietf-srv6ops-srv6-deployment](https://datatracker.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-srv6ops-srv6-deployment)
* **Technical Details:** This draft, in development for nearly two years, outlines migration strategies from various data plane technologies. Recent updates include terminology alignment based on feedback from Edward, and the addition of a section detailing the coexistence of RSVP-TE with SRv6 (incorporating recommendations from RFC 8426).
* **Discussion:** The authors intend to gather input from the BESS working group regarding the VXLAN-to-SRv6 migration section. The draft is nearing readiness for Working Group Last Call (WGLC).

#### [3.2 Problem Summary](https://datatracker.ietf.org/meeting/126/materials/slides-126-srv6ops-srv6-deployment-and-operation-problem-summary-00)
* **Presenter:** Yi Sun Liu (China Mobile)
* **Draft Reference:** [draft-ietf-srv6ops-problem-summary](https://datatracker.ietf.org/html/draft-ietf-srv6ops-problem-summary)
* **Technical Details:** This was the first presentation since the draft's adoption. Updates in version -00 expanded the migration scope to include L2VPN (VPWS and VPLS) and added a concrete comparison of non-aggregatable per-domain prefix allocation versus optimized hierarchical uSID structures. It also rewrote path performance visibility issues (highlighting limitations in current in-band measurement tools) and added a security appendix covering access, cloud, and DC boundaries.

